{"lang":"de","prompt":"＿ Mann ist groß.","options":["der","die","das"],"answer":0,"note":"Mann is masculine → der.","translation":"The man is tall."},
{"lang":"de","prompt":"＿ Frau heißt Anna.","options":["der","die","das"],"answer":1,"note":"Frau is feminine → die.","translation":"The woman is called Anna."},
{"lang":"de","prompt":"＿ Kind spielt.","options":["der","die","das"],"answer":2,"note":"Kind is neuter → das (all -chen/-lein and most young beings).","translation":"The child is playing."},
{"lang":"de","prompt":"＿ Wohnung ist klein.","options":["der","die","das"],"answer":1,"note":"Nouns ending in -ung are always feminine → die.","translation":"The apartment is small."},
{"lang":"de","prompt":"＿ Auto ist neu.","options":["der","die","das"],"answer":2,"note":"Auto is neuter → das.","translation":"The car is new."},
{"lang":"de","prompt":"＿ Mädchen lernt Deutsch.","options":["der","die","das"],"answer":2,"note":"-chen diminutives are always neuter → das, even 'girl'.","translation":"The girl is learning German."},
{"lang":"de","prompt":"＿ Freiheit ist wichtig.","options":["der","die","das"],"answer":1,"note":"-heit/-keit nouns are always feminine → die.","translation":"Freedom is important."},
{"lang":"de","prompt":"＿ Apfel ist rot.","options":["der","die","das"],"answer":0,"note":"Apfel is masculine → der.","translation":"The apple is red."},
{"lang":"de","prompt":"Ich sehe ＿ Mann.","options":["der","den","dem"],"answer":1,"note":"Masculine accusative (direct object) → den.","translation":"I see the man."},
